OL,5, Eight out of 10 South African school   
OL,6, children struggle to read by the age of
OL,7, ten, an international study has found. 
OL,9,FSouth Africa ranked last out of 57     
OL,10,Fcountries assessed in the Progress in  
OL,11,FInternational Reading Literacy Study,  
OL,12,Fwhich tested the reading ability of    
OL,13,F400,000 students globally in 2021.     
OL,15,FIlliteracy among South African children
OL,16,Frose from from 78% in 2016 to 81%.     
OL,18,FThe country's education minister blamed
OL,19,Fthe results on school closures during  
OL,20,Fthe Covid-19 pandemic.                 
